    <body>
     <section name="Deploying in Servlet Container">
      <span class='shortdesc'>Get Hippo CMS up and running 
       in a Java <span class='index' id='servlet_container'>servlet container</span>.</span>
     
       <p>
        To deploy Hippo CMS in a servlet container, the WAR package is used.
        <span class='expire_event'>release</span>Hippo ECM is still under development, 
        but you can already get a snapshot version, see below.
       </p>

      <subsection name="Deploying in Tomcat">

      These deploying steps assume that you have Tomcat installed. If want it, but
      not have it, <a href='install_tomcat.html'>install Tomcat like this</a> first.
      Below, the Tomcat folder will be called $TOMCATDIR. 
 
      <blockquote>
       <table>
        <tr> 
         <td>
            Download 
	 </td>
         <td> 
          <span class='download-48 icon-48'/>
	 </td>
        <td> 
         <a href="http://repo1.maven.org/maven/geronimo-spec/jars/geronimo-spec-jta-1.0-M1.jar">geronimo-spec-jta</a> jar file
            to <code>$TOMCATDIR/lib</code>.
	</td>
        </tr>
          <tr>
         <td>
            Download 
	 </td>
         <td> 
          <span class='download-48 icon-48'/>
	 </td>
   <td>          
     Download the <a href='http://repository.hippocms.org/maven2/org/hippoecm/hippo-ecm-quickstart-war/2.01.00.14160/hippo-ecm-quickstart-war-2.01.00.14160.war'>Hippo CMS WAR</a>
     to the $TOMCATDIR/webapps/ folder renamed to cms.war.
   </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td>Startup</td>
   <td>
    <span class='commandline-48 icon-48'/>
   </td>
   <td>          
       Start Tomcat normally. Tomcat will automatically deploy the cms.war and create an
       cms folder. <a href='help_startup_servlet_container.html'>Need help?</a>
   </td>
   </tr>
  <tr>
   <td>Web Browser</td>
   <td>
    <span class='web-48 icon-48'/>
   </td>
  <td>
     Users can now open the local CMS site 
     <a href="http://localhost:8080/cms/">http://localhost:8080/cms/</a> in 
     their browsers and login as user admin, with password admin.
     <a href='help_web_servlet_container.html'>Need help?</a>
  </td>
  </tr>
       </table>
      </blockquote>
     </subsection>
    </section>
   </body>
</document>
